parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract
the seat belt will not come out of the mechanism
the seat belt buckle will not lock in place
the seat belt is difficult to unlock
the seat belt extends or retracts with light pressure
the seat belt twists up and becomes unable to retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the middle row seat belt can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The middle seat belt will not extend from the retracted position
the middle seat belt is broken
the belt buckle will not lock in place
and when it does lock it is difficult to unlock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the child safety seat buckle can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The built-in child safety seat buckle opens with light pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the rear brake line can cause a loss of braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
The illumination of the disc brake indicator light may indicate a problem with the brake system, which can lead to a loss of braking ability.
symptoms: Disc brake indicator light comes on
especially when making wide left-hand turns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause fires.
symptoms: vehicle comes to an abrupt stop
unable to move in any gear
lunging forward and stopping with a loud sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Cooling Unit and Lines Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the transmission cooling unit and lines can cause the transmission to overheat, leading to failure and potentially causing fires.
The absence of BTSI can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to accidents.
Failure of the seat belts can cause injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Front and middle seat belts not retracting

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs.
Electrical system failures can cause fires, stalling, and other safety hazards, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Smoke or flames coming from the underhood or dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wire harness failures can cause electrical shorts, leading to fires, stalling, and other safety hazards.
Computer module failures can cause stalling, fires, and other safety hazards, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
Alternator failures can cause electrical system failures, leading to stalling, fires, and other safety hazards.
Control console malfunctions can cause electrical system failures, leading to stalling, fires, and other safety hazards.
